<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-09-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="621" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d621">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-09-07"><hi rend="italic">September 7,
                                    1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>German Government strongly urges partition of Samoan Islands, the United
                            States to retain Tutuila and adjacent islets, and England <pb facs="0760" n="664" xml:id="pg_664"/> and Germany to divide the
                            rest. The President is disposed to regard this proposition favorably if
                            details can be satisfactorily arranged with due regard to the national
                            interest and to the welfare of the inhabitants. Ascertain discreetly the
                            views of Her Majesty’s secretary of state for foreign affairs.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>